y-first-century are being fought with precision weapons. Patton Rogers answers two enduring questions: why has precision been such a defining feature of US military thinking? And how has this ambition shaped public and military perceptions of war today?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aMilitary art and sciencezUnited StatesxHistory. 0aTacticsxHistory. 4amanchesterhive variable pricing textbooks. 70(DE-588)4020517-40(DE-627)1063177680(DE-576)208933697aGeschichte2gnd 70(DE-588)4033114-30(DE-627)1043600700(DE-576)209000309aKrieg2gnd 70(DE-588)4288680-60(DE-627)1042804840(DE-576)210824190aZielgenauigkeit2gnd 70(DE-588)7576753-30(DE-627)5328060260(DE-576)26718381XaPräzisionsgelenkte Munition2gnd 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Security (National & International).2bisacsh  aAmerican aircraft.  aCold War.  aFirst World War.  aGulf War.  aJohn F. Kennedy.  aKosovo War.  aNATO.  aPrecision warfare.  aRAND Corporation.  aRobert McNarama.  aRussia-Ukraine war.  aSecond World War.  aUAVs.  aUS military.  aUSAAF.  aatomic bomb.  acontemporary warfare.  adrone warfare.  adrone.  amilitary history.  anuclear war.1 aRogers, James Patton, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2023 eBook-Packagez9783111206455oZDB-23-MUP40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152612589740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526125897423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526125897/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-MUPb2023